{{nihongo|'''Keisuke Gotō'''|後藤 啓介|Gotō Keisuke|born 3 June 2005}} is a Japanese professional [[Association football|footballer]] who plays as a [[Forward (association football)|forward]] for [[Belgian Pro League]] club [[Sint-Truidense V.V.|Sint-Truiden]], on loan from [[R.S.C. Anderlecht|Anderlecht]], and the [[Japan national football team|Japan national team]].

==Club career==

=== Júbilo Iwata ===
Born in [[Hamamatsu]], [[Shizuoka Prefecture]], Gotō joined [[Júbilo Iwata]]'s academy in 2018;<ref name=":0">{{Cite web |date=21 October 2022 |title=「海外で活躍することを期待する選手」磐田U-18FW後藤啓介が"飛び級"昇格「早く皆さんの前でプレーできるように」 |url=https://web.gekisaka.jp/news/jleague/detail/?370832-370832-fl |access-date=3 December 2023 |website=ゲキサカ |language=ja}}</ref> he then came through the club's youth ranks,<ref name=":1">{{Cite web |date=11 January 2023 |title=中盤もこなす万能長身 磐田ＦＷ後藤啓介 |url=https://www.chunichi.co.jp/article/615506 |access-date=3 March 2023 |website=chunichi.co.jp |publisher=[[Chunichi Shimbun]] |language=ja}}</ref><ref name=":2">{{Cite web |title=「高原以来の衝撃！」 磐田17歳の高校2年生FW、3分間2発の鮮烈Jデビュー戦に驚愕「スター候補」「バケモンすぎ」 |url=https://www.football-zone.net/archives/435181 |access-date=3 March 2023 |website=football-zone.net |date=19 February 2023 |publisher= |language=ja}}</ref> while attending Iwata Higashi High School,<ref name=":0" /> and made his first-team debut on 20 July 2022, coming on as a substitute against [[Tokyo Verdy]] in the fourth round of the [[2022 Emperor's Cup|Emperor's Cup]].<ref>{{Cite web |title=Tokyo Verdy vs. Júbilo Iwata - 20 July 2022 |url=https://int.soccerway.com/matches/2022/07/20/japan/emperor-cup/tokyo-verdy-1969/jubilo-iwata/3795413/ |access-date=18 February 2023 |website=Soccerway}}</ref> In October of the same year, he signed his first professional contract with the club.<ref name=":0" /><ref>{{Cite web |date=21 October 2022 |title=ジュビロ磐田U-18 後藤 啓介選手 加入内定のお知らせ |url=https://www.jubilo-iwata.co.jp/newslist/detail/?nw_seq=8589 |access-date=3 December 2023 |website=www.jubilo-iwata.co.jp |publisher=[[Jubilo Iwata]] |language=ja}}</ref>

In January 2023, Gotō was officially promoted to Iwata's senior team ahead of the [[2023 J2 League|2023 J2 League season]].<ref name=":1" /><ref>{{Cite web |date=9 January 2023 |title="補強禁止"の磐田が新体制を発表…大津祐樹が11番から77番に変更、森岡陸が3番に |url=https://web.gekisaka.jp/news/jleague/detail/?376981-376981-fl |access-date=3 December 2023 |website=ゲキサカ |language=ja}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web |last1=Teruya |first1=Ken |last2=Kuroda |first2=Sokichi |date=17 February 2023 |title=勝って高みへ J2きょう開幕、静岡県内3チーム参戦：朝日新聞デジタル |url=https://www.asahi.com/articles/ASR2K7HGNR2JUTPB00R.html?iref=ogimage_rek |access-date=18 February 2023 |website= |publisher=[[Asahi Shimbun]] |language=ja}}</ref> On 18 February 2023, he made his league debut aged 17 years and 260 days, coming on as a substitute for [[Kenyu Sugimoto]] in the 64th minute before scoring a brace in a 2–3 home defeat to [[Fagiano Okayama]], breaking Iwata's club record for youngest scorer previously held by [[Naohiro Takahara]], who scored aged 18 years and 290 days.<ref name=":2" /><ref>{{Cite web |date=18 February 2023 |title=Ｊ２ ジュビロ 開幕戦 黒星スタートも新人が活躍｜NHK 静岡県のニュース |url=https://www3.nhk.or.jp/lnews/shizuoka/20230218/3030019303.html |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20230218114031/https://www3.nhk.or.jp/lnews/shizuoka/20230218/3030019303.html |url-status=dead |archive-date=February 18, 2023 |access-date=18 February 2023 |website=NHK NEWS WEB |publisher=[[NHK]]}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web |date=19 February 2023 |title=暗雲に差した"希望の光"…磐田の17歳FW後藤啓介の豪快ヘッドに脚光「救世主」「スーパー高校生」「将来大物」 |url=https://web.gekisaka.jp/news/jleague/detail/?378752-378752-fl |access-date=3 December 2023 |website=ゲキサカ |language=ja}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web |title=【磐田】17歳260日の後藤啓介が高原超えクラブ最年少弾含む２発も惜敗「喜びと悔しさ半々」 - Ｊ２ : 日刊スポーツ |url=https://www.nikkansports.com/soccer/news/202302180001149.html |access-date=2026-01-15 |website=nikkansports.com |language=ja}}</ref> On March 18, Gotō made his first professional start in a 2–2 draw against [[Shimizu S-Pulse]] in the [[Shizuoka derby]] and scored in the 2nd minute.<ref>{{Cite web |title=ダービー譲らずドロー Ｊ２磐田２度先行も清水追いつく：中日新聞しずおかWeb |url=https://www.chunichi.co.jp/article/656662 |access-date=2026-01-15 |website=中日新聞Web |language=ja}}</ref> Throughout the season, the striker scored seven goals in 33 league appearances for Iwata,<ref name=":3">{{Cite web |last=Goebbels |first=Yannick |date=28 November 2023 |title=C'est officiel : Anderlecht se renforce avec Keisuke Gotō, un Japonais de 18 ans |url=https://www.lesoir.be/552004/article/2023-11-28/cest-officiel-anderlecht-se-renforce-avec-keisuke-goto-un-japonais-de-18-ans |access-date=3 December 2023 |website=[[Le Soir]] |language=fr-BE}}</ref><ref name=":4">{{Cite web |last=Kamata |first=Naohide |date=28 November 2023 |title=【磐田】FW後藤啓介がベルギー１部アンデルレヒトに期限付き移籍発表「必ず成功出来るように」 - Ｊ２ : 日刊スポーツ |url=https://www.nikkansports.com/soccer/news/202311280001143.html |access-date=3 December 2023 |website=[[Nikkan Sports]] |language=ja}}</ref> helping the team finish second in the league table and, as a result, gain promotion back to the [[J1 League]] after a single year of absence.<ref>{{Cite web |last=Ishikawa |first=Hidekazu |date=12 November 2023 |title=【J2】磐田が逆転２位でＪ１昇格、東京Ｖ３位でＪ１昇格ＰＯへ、清水は４位転落／最終節まとめ - Ｊ２ : 日刊スポーツ |url=https://www.nikkansports.com/soccer/news/202311120000645.html |access-date=3 December 2023 |website=Nikkan Sports |language=ja}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web |date=28 November 2023 |title=Football: 18-yr-old Iwata forward Gotō joining Anderlecht on loan |url=https://nordot.app/1102200565131952401?c=445918389795193953 |access-date=3 December 2023 |website=[[Kyodo News]] |language=en |last1=News |first1=Kyodo }}</ref>

=== Anderlecht ===
On 28 November 2023, [[Belgian Pro League]] side [[R.S.C. Anderlecht|Anderlecht]] announced that Gotō would join the team on a season-long loan, with an option-to-buy, starting from 1 January 2024.<ref name=":3" /><ref name=":4" /><ref>{{Cite web |date=28 November 2023 |title=RSC Anderlecht sign Keisuke Gotō |url=https://www.rsca.be/en/Keisuke |access-date=3 December 2023 |website=www.rsca.be |publisher=[[RSC Anderlecht]] |language=en}}</ref> He was initially assigned to the club's reserve team, [[RSCA Futures]].<ref name=":3" /><ref>{{Cite web |last=Lizin |first=Cédric |date=28 November 2023 |title=Anderlecht prépare l'avenir avec l'attaquant japonais Keisuke Gotō, 18 ans |url=https://www.rtbf.be/article/anderlecht-prepare-l-avenir-avec-l-attaquant-japonais-keisuke-goto-18-ans-11293053 |access-date=3 December 2023 |website=[[RTBF]] |language=fr-BE}}</ref>

On 12 January 2024, he made his debut for RSCA Futures, scoring a [[penalty kick]] in a 1–1 [[Challenger Pro League|league]] draw against [[K Beerschot VA|Beerschot]].<ref>{{cite web |date=12 January 2024 |title=Beerschot v RSCA Futures game report |url=https://int.soccerway.com/matches/2024/01/12/belgium/second-division/kfco-wilrijk/belgium-rsc-anderlecht-u23-rsc-anderlecht-ii/4090484/ |access-date=12 January 2024 |publisher=Soccerway}}</ref> Gotō finished the season with six goals and one assist from 14 appearances. On 5 December, Anderlecht permanently signed Gotō until June 2028.<ref>{{Cite web |last=Communications |first=RSCA |date=2024-12-05 |title=Keisuke Goto signs until 2028 |url=https://press.rsca.be/keisuke-goto-signs-until-2028 |access-date=2025-08-06 |website=Royal Sporting Club Anderlecht |language=en}}</ref>

On 16 January 2025, he made his debut for [[R.S.C. Anderlecht|Anderlecht]], coming off the bench in the 40th minute in a 1–0 win against [[Royal Antwerp F.C.|Antwerp]] in the 1st leg of the [[Belgian Cup]] semifinals.<ref>{{Cite web |last=ゲキサカ編集部 |date=2025-01-17 |title=19歳FW後藤啓介がアンデルレヒトでトップチームデビュー!! 191cm長身活かしたポストプレーなどで勝利に貢献 |url=https://web.gekisaka.jp/news/world/detail/?422910-422910-fl |access-date=2026-01-22 |website=ゲキサカ |language=ja}}</ref> On 19 January, Gotō made his league debut against [[K.V. Kortrijk]], replacing [[Luis Vázquez (footballer)|Luis Vázquez]] in the 83rd minute.<ref>{{Cite web |date=2025-01-19 |title=Terugkerende Thorgan Hazard en debuterende Huerta bezorgen matig Anderlecht zege tegen tienkoppig Kortrijk |url=https://www.nieuwsblad.be/sport/voetbal/terugkerende-thorgan-hazard-en-debuterende-huerta-bezorgen-matig-anderlecht-zege-tegen-tienkoppig-kortrijk/35059368.html |access-date=2026-01-22 |website=Nieuwsblad |language=nl-BE}}</ref> On 26 January, he made his first start for Anderlecht, scoring a [[Header (association football)|header]] in the 24th minute assisted by [[Thorgan Hazard]] in a 4–1 victory against [[K.V. Mechelen]].<ref>{{Cite web |date=2025-01-26 |title=Efficiënt Anderlecht spoelt Europese kater door en wint met ruime cijfers van KV Mechelen |url=https://www.nieuwsblad.be/sport/voetbal/efficient-anderlecht-spoelt-europese-kater-door-en-wint-met-ruime-cijfers-van-kv-mechelen/36065338.html |access-date=2026-01-22 |website=Nieuwsblad |language=nl-BE}}</ref> On 30 January, Gotō made his [[UEFA Europa League]] debut against [[TSG 1899 Hoffenheim]], in which he scored in the 79th minute, making the game 2–4. Anderlecht went on to lose the match 3–4.<ref>{{Cite web |last=UEFA.com |title=History: Anderlecht 3-4 Hoffenheim {{!}} UEFA Europa League 2024/25 |url=https://www.uefa.com/uefaeuropaleague/match/2042220--anderlecht-vs-hoffenheim/ |access-date=2025-08-06 |website=UEFA.com |language=en}}</ref> Gotō spent most of the 2024–25 season with RSCA Futures, making 16 appearances for them; scoring seven while assisting two. For Anderlecht, Gotō made ten appearances in all competitions and scored three goals.<ref>{{Cite web |title=Keisuke Goto Stats, Goals, Records, Assists, Cups and more |url=https://fbref.com/en/players/82a2ca86/Keisuke-Goto |access-date=2025-08-08 |website=FBref.com |language=en}}</ref>

==== Loan to Sint-Truiden ====
On 7 August 2025, Gotō was loaned out to fellow Belgian Pro League club [[Sint-Truidense V.V.|Sint-Truiden]] on a deal excluding an option to buy.<ref>{{Cite web |title=Keisuke Goto joins STVV on loan {{!}} RSCA Youth |url=https://neerpede.rsca.be/en/good-luck-goto |access-date=2025-08-08 |website=neerpede.rsca.be |language=en}}</ref> Gotō played his first game for Sint-Truiden on 8 August against [[F.C.V. Dender E.H.|Dender]], coming on in the 80th minute for [[Andrés Ferrari]].<ref>{{Cite web |title=Sint-Truiden vs Dender: First Division A stats & head-to-head |url=https://www.bbc.com/sport/football/live/cy40v8k4ev7t |access-date=2025-08-14 |website=BBC Sport |language=en-GB}}</ref> Gotō scored his first goal for Sint-Truiden against [[RAAL La Louvière|La Louvière]] in the 91st minute assisted by [[Rihito Yamamoto]] on 17 August, making the game 2–1.<ref>{{Cite web |title=Sint-Truiden vs. Raal La Louviere Box Score and Stats - August 17, 2025 |url=https://www.foxsports.com/soccer/juliper-league-sint-truiden-vs-raal-la-louviere-aug-17-2025-game-boxscore-627983?tab=boxscore |access-date=2025-08-18 |website=www.foxsports.com |language=en-US}}</ref> On 3 December, Gotō scored a brace in a 3–3 draw against [[Antwerp FC|Antwerp]] in the [[Croky Cup]]. However, Sint-Truiden lost the game on penalties, eliminating them from the tournament.<ref>{{Cite web |title=野澤大志ブランドンがPK戦で2本ストップ! 日本代表対決で後藤啓介に2G1Aを許すも8強進出に貢献（ゲキサカ） |url=https://news.yahoo.co.jp/articles/16228a9429d39db2dbdf7eab8872d38f3bfcf567 |access-date=2025-12-04 |website=Yahoo!ニュース |language=ja}}</ref> On 26 December, Gotō scored another brace, this time against [[Standard Liège]] in a 2–1 win in the Pro League.<ref>{{Cite web |title=Goto Double Lifts STVV Past Standard Liège In Thriller |url=https://evrimagaci.org/gpt/goto-double-lifts-stvv-past-standard-liege-in-thriller-521494 |access-date=2026-01-02 |website=Grand Pinnacle Tribune |language=en}}</ref> On 16 January 2026, Gotō won the Pro League December Player of the Month award after scoring three goals with one assist.<ref name=PlayeroftheMonth>{{Cite web |last=Franken |first=Christophe |date=2026-01-19 |title=Keisuke Goto (Saint-Trond) est le joueur du mois en Pro League : "Je suis prêt à être titulaire à Anderlecht mais on verra ça après la Coupe du monde" |url=https://www.dhnet.be/sports/football/division-1a/2026/01/16/keisuke-goto-saint-trond-est-le-joueur-du-mois-en-pro-league-je-suis-pret-a-etre-titulaire-a-anderlecht-mais-on-verra-ca-apres-la-coupe-du-monde-YMT37ZAZ7VBKTF4CGOYVDATE2A/ |access-date=2026-01-19 |website=DHnet |language=fr}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web |last=ゲキサカ編集部 |date=2026-01-18 |title=後藤啓介がベルギー・リーグ月間MVP!! アンデルレヒト17歳MFに連絡「今回は僕の名前が入っている」 |url=https://web.gekisaka.jp/news/world/detail/?445064-445064-fl |access-date=2026-01-19 |website=ゲキサカ |language=ja}}</ref> On 21 February, Gotō assisted twice in a 2–1 win against [[FCV Dender EH|Dender]].<ref>{{Cite web |last=ゲキサカ編集部 |date=2026-02-22 |title=伊藤涼太郎1G1A、後藤啓介2A、山本理仁1G!! 谷口彰悟も長距離ドリブルでゴール関与のシントトロイデンが3連勝 |url=https://web.gekisaka.jp/news/world/detail/?446744-446744-fl |access-date=2026-05-16 |website=ゲキサカ |language=ja}}</ref> On 3 May, Gotō caused controversy after celebrating a 2–0 win against parent club [[RSC Anderlecht|Anderlecht]] at full-time after scoring in the 75th minute, which infuriated some players on the opposition side. This incident created speculation that Gotō might not play for Anderlecht again.<ref>{{Cite web |last=東スポWEB |date=2026-04-24 |title=後藤啓介が一触即発！ 過剰アピールにアンデルレヒト激怒「あんなに喜ぶべきじゃない」 |url=https://news.jp/i/1420205963219173423 |access-date=2026-05-13 |website=NEWSjp |language=ja}}</ref> On 12 May, Gotō helped Sint-Truiden confirm their place in a [[UEFA|European competition]] next season after a 0–2 loss against [[Club Brugge KV|Club Brugge]], the first time since 2003.<ref>{{Cite web |last=サカノワスタッフ |date=2026-05-12 |title=シント＝トロイデン3位で欧州切符。20歳FW後藤啓介のW杯日本代表選出なるか |url=https://sakanowa.jp/topics/108259 |access-date=2026-05-16 |language=ja}}</ref>

== International career ==
Gotō was a youth international for Japan, having represented the [[Japan national under-18 football team|under-18 national team]].<ref>{{Cite web |date=22 November 2022 |title=【Match Report】U-17 Japan National Team win over Denmark to claim title - International U-18 Friendly Tournament |url=https://www.jfa.jp/eng/national_team/u17_2022/news/00031064/ |access-date=3 December 2023 |website=www.jfa.jp |publisher=[[Japan Football Association]] |language=ja}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web |date=25 November 2023 |title=クロアチア遠征のU-17日本代表がU-18デンマークに快勝。2勝1敗でInternational U-18 Friendly Tournament制覇 |url=https://web.gekisaka.jp/news/japan/detail/?373644-373644-fl |access-date=3 December 2023 |website=ゲキサカ |language=ja}}</ref>

On 6 November 2025, Gotō was called up to play for [[Japan national football team|Japan]] by head coach [[Hajime Moriyasu]] to play in the [[Kirin Challenge Cup]] for a set a matches against [[Ghana national football team|Ghana]] and [[Bolivia national football team|Bolivia]].<ref>{{Cite web |title=SAMURAI BLUE (Japan National Team) squad & schedule - KIRIN CHALLENGE CUP 2025 vs Ghana (11/14＠Aichi) vs Bolivia (11/18＠Tokyo) |url=https://www.jfa.jp/eng/samuraiblue/20251114/news/00035719/ |access-date=2025-11-14 |website=www.jfa.jp |language=ja}}</ref> On 15 November, Gotō made his national team debut when he replaced [[Ayase Ueda]] in the 75th minute in a 2–0 win against Ghana.<ref>{{Cite web |title=北野颯太＆後藤啓介が日本代表デビュー！ 19歳佐藤龍之介も含めた“若手3人衆”に森保監督が期待すること（サッカーキング） |url=https://news.yahoo.co.jp/articles/f9521b3838ca0342a9af0b9caf8ba15aac071688 |access-date=2025-11-14 |website=Yahoo!ニュース |language=ja}}</ref>

On 19 March 2026, Gotō was selected for Japan's friendlies against [[Scotland national football team|Scotland]] and [[England national football team|England]].<ref>{{Cite web |date=2026-03-19 |title=日本代表、イギリス遠征招集メンバーを発表！ 冨安健洋が復帰、塩貝健人が初招集…W杯メンバー発表最後のテストマッチ {{!}} Goal.com 日本 |url=https://www.goal.com/jp/%E3%83%8B%E3%83%A5%E3%83%BC%E3%82%B9/20260319-japan-member-scotland-england/blt9601830d16f03e87 |access-date=2026-05-13 |website=www.goal.com |language=ja}}</ref> On 29 March, Gotō made his first international start against Scotland, but failed to find the back of the net.<ref>{{Cite web |title=新たな才能発見！？ サッカー日本代表、後藤啓介がメンバー入りへ前進？スコットランドに通用した隠れたプレー（フットボールチャンネル） |url=https://news.yahoo.co.jp/articles/6fa1f691970bfcc3e76831efc38aaef1f7a6cf78 |access-date=2026-05-13 |website=Yahoo!ニュース |language=ja}}</ref>

On 15 May 2026, Gotō was selected in Japan's 26-man roster for the [[2026 FIFA World Cup]].<ref>{{Cite web |url=https://www.fifa.com/en/news/articles/japan-squad-announcement |access-date=2026-05-16 |website=www.fifa.com|title=Mitoma misses out as Japan squad named}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web |title=【日本代表】 DF谷口彰悟選手、FW後藤啓介選手がFIFAワールドカップ2026™️に臨むSAMURAI BLUEメンバーに選出 |url=https://stvv.jp/news/team/20260515_1/ |access-date=2026-05-16 |website=STVV（シント＝トロイデンVV）日本公式サイト |language=ja}}</ref> He was the youngest member of the squad.<ref>{{Cite web |title=W杯日本代表最年少の20歳・後藤啓介「ワクワクが止まらない」191センチ大型FW、国際Aマッチ3試合での選出に笑顔（中日スポーツ） |url=https://news.yahoo.co.jp/articles/8a1804d76a90c009bb4923ccb8ce206cb81adc1f |access-date=2026-05-16 |website=Yahoo!ニュース |language=ja}}</ref>

== Personal life ==
On 31 March 2026, in response to being compared to [[Erling Haaland]], Gotō revealed that his footballing idol was [[Harry Kane]], who plays for [[Bundesliga]] club [[FC Bayern Munich|Bayern Munich]]. Gotō also mentioned that he tries to imitate [[Shunsuke Nakamura]]'s free-kick technique.<ref>{{Cite web |title=「ああいう名手がいる間に聞きたい」後藤啓介が中村俊輔コーチにFK伝授を志願「元から蹴り方は真似している」【日本代表】 {{!}} サッカーダイジェストWeb |url=https://www.soccerdigestweb.com/news/detail/id=191634 |access-date=2026-06-07 |website=www.soccerdigestweb.com |language=ja}}</ref>

